C# has anonymous types, which are closer to records, but there&#x27;s no way to refer to a particular type structure.<p>So while I can write<p><pre><code>    var x = { FirstName = &quot;Riff&quot;, LastName = &quot;Raff&quot; }
</code></pre>
and then go ahead and access x.FirstName and x.LastName, I can&#x27;t declare a method signature like this:<p><pre><code>    void Display({ string FirstName, string LastName } nameRecord)
    {
    }
</code></pre>
This is the kind of thing which is being proposed (along with possible pattern matching/decomposition syntax which is new ground for C#)
